Flagging off the training in Minna, the state coordinator, Alhaji Abdulmalik Liman said the beneficiaries consisted of both male and female selected from the 25 local government areas of the state. He reminded the beneficiaries that NDE is not providing white collar jobs but skills acquisition to enable them to be self-reliant and independent economically. He also informed that the trainees are given free feeding, paid stipends to be certified and educated on CBN windows and other financial institutions available to provide funding for their businesses in order to boost their economic base. The beneficiaries lauded NDE for the initiative and the opportunity given to them while assuring the agency that they would live up to expectation